      <Meanings>
        <Meaning id="22df5994-dad9-4f5a-8dc5-455be544d1da" type="Noun">
          <Vi>Dầu mỏ</Vi>
          <En>A naturally occurring, unrefined liquid hydrocarbon mixture found beneath the Earth's surface, used as fuel and raw material for chemicals.</En>
          <Example>Crude petroleum must be refined before it can be used to produce gasoline, diesel, and other products.</Example>
          <IsArchaic>false</IsArchaic>
          <Situations>
            <Situation id="45242b5c-f33a-41ff-aeaf-75daa5837134">
              <Vi>Ngành khai thác dầu mỏ tại các mỏ dưới lòng đất hoặc biển.</Vi>
              <En>The extraction of crude oil from underground or offshore reservoirs.</En>
            </Situation>
            <Situation id="0f7e0c69-cdd4-4093-a7ba-16f0d3bd05b1">
              <Vi>Quá trình tinh chế dầu mỏ thành các sản phẩm như xăng, dầu diesel.</Vi>
              <En>The refining process that converts crude petroleum into usable fuels and petrochemicals.</En>
            </Situation>
